NeighbourCart — Project Submission
Author: Huzaifa Kopty

Project Overview:
NeighbourCart is a simple web-based project created as part of my learning and internship submission.
The idea behind this project is to show a basic neighbourhood shopping concept using a clean and easy-to-use interface.

How to Open the Project:
1. Download and unzip the project folder.
2. Open index.html using any modern browser (Chrome or Edge recommended).
3. Go to the Projects section.
4. Click on “Open NeighbourCart” to view the NeighbourCart project.

Demo Video Guidelines (3–10 minutes):
In the demo video, the following is demonstrated:
- Showing the project folder and main files (index.html, style.css, neighbourcart.html).
- Opening the portfolio website in the browser.
- Navigating through the About and Skills sections.
- Opening NeighbourCart from the Projects section.
- Demonstrating product cards, listings, and basic interactions.
- Showing responsiveness by resizing the browser window.
- Ending the video on the Contact section.

Notes:
- No GitHub repository is used; all project files are included locally.
- This project is built using HTML and CSS, with minimal JavaScript where required.
- The project is created for learning and practice purposes.

Declaration:
I confirm that this project was developed by me as part of my learning process.
